        <Parent_String>building plans [300034157], plans (orthographic projections) [300034104], orthographic projections (images) [300034017], images by method of projection [300068504], images by method of representation [300033974], visual works by form of image [300191088], visual works by form [300191087], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawings or works in another medium, often made by an engineer, that indicate the location of utilities, including water supply lines, fire hydrants, sewage disposal lines, and other utilities typically located in the road right-of-way. As part of the construction process, these plans are generally required for submission to local authorities such as public works departments, public health boards, fire departments, pollution control regulators, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000001131/Ramsey and Sleeper, Architectural Graphics Standards (1981)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a dibujos, a menudo realizados por un ingeniero, que indican la localización de los servicios, incluyendo las líneas de sumnistro de agua, bocas de fuego, líneas de eliminación de aguas residuales y otros servicios, usualmente localizados en la vía con derecho a paso. Como parte del proceso de construcción, estos planos generalmente so requeridos para proponer a las autoridades locales, tales como departamentos de obras públicas, juntas de salud pública, departamentos de bomberos, control de contaminación, etc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar tekeningen, vaak door een ingenieur gemaakt, die de locatie aangeven van nutsvoorzieningen, met inbegrip van waterleidingen, brandkranen, rioleringen en andere voorzieningen welke zich meestal op of onder de openbare weg bevinden. Als onderdeel van de bouwprocedure dienen deze tekeningen doorgaans ter goedkeuring te worden voorgelegd aan lokale overheidsinstellingen, zoals openbare werken, gezondheidsinstanties, brandweerdiensten, milieucontrole-instanties enzovoort.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一由工程師繪製的圖則或其他媒材的作品，用於標示公用設施的位置，如供水管道、消防栓、污水處理管道，以及其他位於路權軌道上的公用設施。作為建築過程的一部分，這類平面圖一般需呈報有關當局如工務處、衛生局、消防局、污染管制單位等等。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zeichnung oder Arbeit in einem anderen Medium, oft von einem Ingenieur angefertigt, die alle Installationen anzeigt, wie Wasserversorgungsrohre, Feuerhydranten, Abwasserrohre und andere typische, in den Hauptstraßen befindliche Installationen. Diese Pläne sind in der Regel Teil des Bauprozesses und werden zur Genehmigung von örtlichen Institutionen wie Bauämtern, Gesundheitsämtern, Brandschadenabteilungen, Umweltämtern etc. verlangt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Desenhos ou trabalhos em outro meio, frequentemente feitos por um engenheiro, que indicam a localização de serviços de utilidade pública, incluindo sistemas de abastecimento de água, extintores de incêndio, esgotos e outros serviços. Como parte do processo de construção, essas plantas são geralmente necessárias para submissão às autoridades locais tais como departamentos públicos. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
